Program: Discovery
Title: Weathering the Storm - snow and avalanches
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryt4
Last Broadcast Date: 04 October 2004
An avalanche is defined as a large mass of snow, which plunges down a mountainside. The fourth in a series on the world's most extreme weather. This programme explores what happens when there is an avalanche and examines how the people in the Swiss Alps, one of the wettest and coldest areas of Switzerland, predict and prepare for avalanches. Show less